The paper deals with the use of deep convolutional neural networks (ConvNets) for identifying phototoxicity in label-free microscopy images of cells. This falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV) as it involves the analysis of images using machine learning techniques. The use of ConvNets also suggests that the paper may fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper discusses the interpretability of the trained ConvNet, which suggests that it may also fall under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR).
